00:10:36,210 --> 00:10:38,860
今年  我们要改变一下出场方式
Uh, this year, we're handling the arrival a bit differently.

173
00:10:38,860 --> 00:10:41,860
您将先被护送去圆形大厅与领导层合影
You'll be escorted to the rotunda for a photo op with the leadership

174
00:10:41,860 --> 00:10:44,160
然后再去等候室
before going to the holding room.

175
00:10:44,160 --> 00:10:45,510
我不需要去等候室
I don't need to go to the holding room.

176
00:10:45,510 --> 00:10:47,510
你直接带我去大厅
You can take me directly to the gallery.

177
00:10:47,510 --> 00:10:50,110
没关系  都听第一夫人的
Yes, that's fine. Whatever the First Lady prefers.

178
00:10:50,110 --> 00:10:52,160
之后我们需要分两个车队
And we'll need two separate motorcades after.

179
00:10:52,160 --> 00:10:54,400
我要直接去机场
I'll be going straight to the airport.

180
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:56,690
-那就两个车队  -是  先生
- Two motorcades, then. - Yes, sir.

181
00:10:57,310 --> 00:10:59,180
我想向你们汇报一下特别来宾名单
I'd like to brief you on the list of special guests attending--

182
00:10:59,180 --> 00:11:01,190
看上去没什么问题
This all seems pretty straightforward.

183
00:11:01,190 --> 00:11:02,130
如果你觉得没问题我也没问题
I'm good if you are.

184
00:11:02,130 --> 00:11:04,500
嗯  没问题  多谢你了
Yes, I'm fine. Thank you so very much.

185
00:11:09,550 --> 00:11:10,740
你有空吗
Do you have a moment?

186
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:15,160
伊丽莎白怎么样了
How's Elizabeth?

187
00:11:15,620 --> 00:11:17,190
她让我代她问好
She sends her regards.

188
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,770
当然了
I'll bet she does.

189
00:11:18,770 --> 00:11:19,990
竞选呢
And the campaign?

190
00:11:21,420 --> 00:11:23,480
还在探讨可行性
Still exploring viability.

191
00:11:24,020 --> 00:11:25,370
桃瑞丝还没答应吗
Doris isn't on board yet?

192
00:11:25,370 --> 00:11:26,470
回头就知道了
Uh, we'll see.

193
00:11:27,150 --> 00:11:28,500
你给了她什么
What have you offered her?

194
00:11:29,870 --> 00:11:32,620
我想先跟莉安策划一个稳妥的竞选策略
Well, I want to put together a solid campaign strategy with LeAnn

195
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:34,970
再跟她二次接触
before engaging her again.

196
00:11:34,970 --> 00:11:36,780
如果你需要我帮忙  就告诉我
Well, if you need my help, let me know.

197
00:11:36,780 --> 00:11:38,840
我当党鞭时  我们关系很好
She and I were very close when I was whip.

198
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:41,820
-你的事够多了  -不麻烦的
- You've got a lot on your plate. - No, it's no trouble at all.

199
00:11:42,270 --> 00:11:43,420
我再找你吧
I'll let you know.

200
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:45,160
今晚见
See you tonight.

201
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,220
可以开始准备了吗  先生
You ready to prep, sir?

202
00:12:02,220 --> 00:12:05,360
-我要做些改动  -我去叫讲稿撰写人
- I need to make some changes. - I'll call the speech writers.

203
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:07,790
不用  我自己来  去把克丽丝塔找来
No, I wanna do these myself. And track down Calista.

204
00:12:07,790 --> 00:12:09,620
我们还可以再加一名宾客
We have to make room for one more guest.

205
00:12:09,620 --> 00:12:10,570
是  先生
Yes, sir.

206
00:12:37,150 --> 00:12:38,140
怎么回事
What's that?

207
00:12:39,170 --> 00:12:40,690
我要把文身洗掉
I'm having it removed.

208
00:12:43,350 --> 00:12:45,100
太可惜了  我挺喜欢呢
Well, that's too bad. I liked it.

209
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:47,630
该向前看了
Hmm, time to move on.

210
00:12:47,970 --> 00:12:49,040
后面是什么
From what?

211
00:12:50,710 --> 00:12:52,810
需要文身的我
From the me that needed a tattoo.

212
00:12:53,820 --> 00:12:55,200
我没多少时间
I don't have much time.

213
00:12:56,350 --> 00:12:58,130
你什么时候得去首都
When do you have to be at the Capitol?

214
00:12:58,610 --> 00:12:59,950
不到一小时后
Less than an hour.

215
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:03,780
-威士忌还是伏特加  -伏特加
- Whiskey or vodka? - Vodka.

216
00:13:07,540 --> 00:13:09,810
你对桃瑞丝·琼斯有多了解
How well do you know Doris Jones?

217
00:13:09,810 --> 00:13:14,070
见过她几次  不怎么了解
Oh, uh, met her a few times. I don't know her that well, though.

218
00:13:14,670 --> 00:13:16,510
-怎么  -她女儿  西莉娅
- Why? - Her daughter, Celia,

219
00:13:16,510 --> 00:13:18,240
希望我帮他们弄到拨款
wants me to help them get appropriations 

220
00:13:18,450 --> 00:13:20,160
筹建一家乳腺癌诊所
for a breast cancer clinic.

221
00:13:20,220 --> 00:13:23,910
作为回报  他们愿用德州的钱资助我的竞选
In return, they want to pad my campaign with Texas money.

222
00:13:23,910 --> 00:13:25,900
-多少  -三百万
- How much? - Three million.

223
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:27,790
可能还不止
To start. 

224
00:13:28,150 --> 00:13:30,220
她的选区才没那么多钱
Her district doesn't have that kind of money.

225
00:13:30,220 --> 00:13:33,110
西莉娅说他们的捐助人是30区以外的
Celia says they're courting donors from outside the 30th.

226
00:13:33,110 --> 00:13:34,450
但我一个助手
But one of my aides 

227
00:13:34,450 --> 00:13:37,200
听说克莱尔·安德伍德和莉安·哈维
heard that Claire Underwood and LeAnn Harvey

228
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:38,870
今天去了琼斯的办公室
were in Jones' office today.

229
00:13:42,410 --> 00:13:44,480
莉安我认识
LeAnn's someone I know.

230
00:13:46,020 --> 00:13:48,450
格兰顿-希尔几年前想把她挖来
Glendon Hill was courting her a few years ago.

231
00:13:48,780 --> 00:13:50,240
她拒绝了你吗
Did she turn you down?

232
00:13:51,010 --> 00:13:52,340
我们请不起她
We couldn't afford her.

233
00:13:54,490 --> 00:13:56,950
我知道你已经金盆洗手了  但这笔钱不是小数
Look, I know you're out of the game, but this is a lot of money.

234
00:13:56,950 --> 00:13:59,770
如果是真  能帮我大忙  如果不是...
If it's legit, it could really help me. But if it's not, I--

235
00:13:59,770 --> 00:14:01,980
我去跟莉安谈谈  看能问出什么来
I'll talk to LeAnn and see what I can find out.

236
00:14:03,780 --> 00:14:04,740
给
Here.

237
00:14:06,970 --> 00:14:09,060
我想先尝你
I want to taste you first.

238
00:15:06,850 --> 00:15:08,720
下面是特别报道
This is a special report.

239
00:15:08,890 --> 00:15:11,530
弗兰西斯·安德伍德总统向国会联席会议
President Francis Underwood's State of the Union address

240
00:15:11,530 --> 00:15:13,210
发布国情咨文讲话
to a joint session of Congress.

241
00:15:15,420 --> 00:15:17,880
今晚  世界的眼睛都盯着华盛顿
Tonight the eyes of the world are on Washington.

242
00:15:18,090 --> 00:15:21,060
安德伍德总统几分钟后就将上台
President Underwood will take the stage in just a few minutes...

243
00:15:22,660 --> 00:15:24,160
把食物拿走
Take the food away.

244
00:15:24,390 --> 00:15:26,060
您午饭就没吃  黑尔太太
You didn't eat your lunch, Mrs. Hale.

245
00:15:26,060 --> 00:15:28,020
我不舒服
Yeah, well, I didn't feel well.

246
00:15:28,020 --> 00:15:29,850
那您就更该吃点晚饭了  您的药
Then you really should eat dinner. Your medication--

247
00:15:29,850 --> 00:15:31,970
别让我再说一遍了  迈克尔
Please don't make me ask you again, Michael.

248
00:15:31,970 --> 00:15:34,980
拿走  这味儿熏得我难受
Just take it away. The smell of it is making me ill.

249
00:15:35,950 --> 00:15:36,930
是  夫人
Yes, ma'am.

250
00:15:40,050 --> 00:15:44,060
女士们先生们  美国第一夫人
Ladies and gentlemen, the First Lady of the United States.

251
00:16:00,980 --> 00:16:04,070
-西莉娅  -谢谢你的安排
- Celia. - Thank you so much for arranging this.

252
00:16:04,170 --> 00:16:06,650
能坐在你旁边太荣幸了
It's a big honor to be sitting next to you.

253
00:16:21,830 --> 00:16:26,310
议长先生  有请美国总统
Mr. Speaker, the President of the United States.

254
00:17:06,780 --> 00:17:08,940
在这里看国情咨文真有意思
Interesting place to watch the SOTU.

255
00:17:10,110 --> 00:17:13,660
这样更好玩  跟人民大众在一起
It's more fun this way. You know, hanging with the hoi polloi.

256
00:17:14,910 --> 00:17:16,500
你为什么来华府
So, what brings you to D.C.?

257
00:17:16,620 --> 00:17:19,710
国会都到齐了  适合揽活儿干
Well, all of Congress in town, it's good for hustling work.

258
00:17:19,710 --> 00:17:22,550
你什么时候揽过活儿  你从来都是拒绝别人
Since when do you hustle? You turn people away.

259
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:24,440
你怎么知道我在这儿
How'd you know I was in town?

260
00:17:24,650 --> 00:17:27,200
我虽然退休了  但我还是眼观六路耳听八方
I might be retired, but I still have my ear to the ground.

261
00:17:27,970 --> 00:17:31,760
是真的喽  伟大的雷米·丹顿解甲归田了
So that's true? The great Remy Danton has hung up his jersey?

262
00:17:33,030 --> 00:17:34,520
我从未这么痛快过
I've never felt better.

263
00:17:35,070 --> 00:17:37,610
-你不是来跟我寒暄的吧  -不是
- Don't tell me this is a social visit. - No.

264
00:17:37,940 --> 00:17:40,210
-如果不是为公事  -是公事
- Well, if it isn't business... - It's business.

265
00:17:40,210 --> 00:17:41,810
-各位国会议员  -好吧
- Members of Congress... - Okay.

266
00:17:41,810 --> 00:17:43,280
-我十分荣幸  -那么
- ...I have the high privilege... - So...

267
00:17:43,280 --> 00:17:45,920
-等等  节目开始了  -为各位请出
- Oh, hold on. The show is starting. - ...of presenting to you,

268
00:17:45,920 --> 00:17:47,950
美国总统
the President of the United States.

269
00:17:59,890 --> 00:18:00,890
谢谢
Thank you.

270
00:18:02,530 --> 00:18:03,740
非常感谢
Thank you so much.

271
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:09,280
谢谢  议长先生  副总统先生
Thank you. Mr. Speaker, Mr. Vice President,

272
00:18:09,310 --> 00:18:12,320
各位国会议员  我的美国同胞们
members of Congress, my fellow Americans.

273
00:18:13,020 --> 00:18:14,080
一年前
One year ago,

274
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:17,200
我第一次做这番讲话
when I gave this address for the first time,

275
00:18:17,630 --> 00:18:21,390
当时我国处于完全不同的一个时期
it was during a very different period for our country.

276
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:25,160
我国正在从一起政治丑闻和
Our nation was recovering from a political scandal

277
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:27,690
与中国的贸易危机中走出来
and a trade crisis with China.

278
00:18:28,060 --> 00:18:32,280
而你们面前的  是一位未经过选举的总统
Before you stood a president no one had elected.

279
00:18:32,570 --> 00:18:35,570
但现在  那个人依然站在你们面前
But that same man stands before you now,

280
00:18:35,570 --> 00:18:37,530
而黑暗时期已经过去
and the darkness is behind us.

281
00:18:37,530 --> 00:18:41,130
国家现在情势大好  前途愈发光明
The state of the union is bright, and getting brighter.

282
00:18:48,830 --> 00:18:50,930
我们遭遇过挑战  没错
We've had our challenges, yes.

283
00:18:50,940 --> 00:18:52,760
尤其是跟俄国
Particularly with Russia.

284
00:18:52,880 --> 00:18:55,550
的确有些很紧张的时刻
There were some tense moments, to be sure,

285
00:18:55,550 --> 00:18:58,390
但我们还是克服了那些紧张
and yet we overcame those tensions.

286
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:01,740
佩特罗夫总统让我们继续建立信任
President Petrov let us continue to build trust

287
00:19:01,740 --> 00:19:05,450
并表现出我们已从去年的经历中吸取了教训
and show that we've learned from our experiences last year.

288
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:08,490
我个人想感谢第一夫人
And I'd personally like to acknowledge the First Lady,

289
00:19:08,490 --> 00:19:12,520
她为修复两国关系带了路
who led the way in repairing those burned bridges.

290
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:22,110
她得到的掌声比总统还多
She's getting more applause than the president.

291
00:19:22,810 --> 00:19:24,200
对你是好事吧
Good for you, isn't it?

292
00:19:25,950 --> 00:19:27,680
好厉害的客户
Quite a high-profile client.

293
00:19:28,280 --> 00:19:29,350
谁告诉你的
Who told you that?

294
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:32,860
-只是一猜  -不  你猜错了
- Just a guess. - No, you guessed wrong.

295
00:19:35,640 --> 00:19:38,260
你知道有财大气粗的德州捐助人
So what do you know about big Texas donors...

296
00:19:38,780 --> 00:19:40,630
就为了达拉斯一个穷选区
who care enough about a poor Dallas district

297
00:19:40,630 --> 00:19:43,470
会给加州的竞选捐钱吗
to donate money to a campaign in California?

298
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:45,400
我没听说过
That went right over my head.

299
00:19:46,290 --> 00:19:49,530
第一夫人去了达拉斯  你当时也在
First Lady was in Dallas. You were in Dallas.

300
00:19:49,820 --> 00:19:50,760
第一夫人来了这儿
The First Lady is here. 

301
00:19:50,760 --> 00:19:51,920
你也来了
Now you're here.

302
00:19:52,660 --> 00:19:56,710
我觉得你是太闲了  雷米
I think you have far too much time on your hands, Remy.

303
00:19:57,120 --> 00:19:59,350
这笔钱上到处是你的痕迹
Your fingerprints are all over this money.

304
00:20:07,550 --> 00:20:09,650
你现在为杰姬·夏普工作了
You're working for Jackie Sharp now?

305
00:20:10,330 --> 00:20:12,450
不  只是朋友
No. Just friends.

306
00:20:14,030 --> 00:20:17,040
-只是朋友吗  -嗯
- Just friends, huh? - Yeah.

307
00:20:19,540 --> 00:20:22,020
我觉得她身上也到处是你的痕迹
I think your fingerprints are all over her.

308
00:20:25,290 --> 00:20:26,400
这样如何
How about this?

309
00:20:27,830 --> 00:20:31,240
你别来刺探我的事
You don't poke around in my shit...

310
00:20:31,820 --> 00:20:33,880
我就不去刺探你的
and I won't poke around in yours.

311
00:20:34,940 --> 00:20:38,040
见到你很高兴  雷米  别退休就变怂了
It was good to see you, Remy. Don't get too soft in retirement.

312
00:20:41,830 --> 00:20:43,140
一般来说
Now, it's considered uncouth

313
00:20:43,140 --> 00:20:45,510
正在进行竞选的总统
for a president who's in the midst of a campaign,

314
00:20:45,510 --> 00:20:49,110
不该直接谈论即将到来的竞选  但今晚
to talk directly about the upcoming election, but tonight,

315
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:50,430
我觉得我必须谈
I feel compelled.

316
00:20:50,430 --> 00:20:53,140
因为我们选民即将在
Because the votes our electorate casts

317
00:20:53,250 --> 00:20:56,900
目前的初选和11月的大选中投的票
during the current primaries and the general election in November

318
00:20:56,910 --> 00:21:01,390
将对在做的各位有深远的影响
will have a profound impact on everyone in this room.

319
00:21:01,390 --> 00:21:06,610
有些人  包括我  可能将失业
Some of us, myself included, may find ourselves out of a job.

320
00:21:07,160 --> 00:21:09,030
如果我们想保住工作
If we want to keep our jobs,

321
00:21:09,080 --> 00:21:11,430
我们就得聆听美国民众的声音
we have to listen to the American people.

322
00:21:11,430 --> 00:21:14,600
我们就得更加努力  实现目标
We have to work harder! We have to deliver!

323
00:21:18,950 --> 00:21:21,470
就像桃瑞丝·琼斯
Just like Doris Jones.

324
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:25,760
她已经在国会任职了34年
She has kept her job in Congress for 34 years

325
00:21:25,760 --> 00:21:29,860
因为她从未向逆境低过头
because she never relented in the face of adversity.

326
00:21:29,860 --> 00:21:34,030
事实上  就在今天  她还为一家她已经争取了
In fact, just today, she called me about a breast cancer clinic

327
00:21:34,030 --> 00:21:37,370
十年的乳腺癌诊所给我打电话
she has been fighting for over the past decade.

328
00:21:37,370 --> 00:21:39,050
她的计划很大胆
Now, her plan is bold.

329
00:21:39,150 --> 00:21:42,640
将退伍军人医院扩张  向普通民众开放
A VA hospital expansion open to the general public,

330
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:44,240
由联邦资金资助
financed by federal money.

331
00:21:44,250 --> 00:21:49,260
这一大胆计划能通过科普  筛查
A bold plan that will significantly increase successful diagnoses

332
00:21:49,260 --> 00:21:53,720
和可负担医保  大幅提升确诊和治疗的成功率
and treatment through education, screenings, and affordable care.

333
00:22:00,170 --> 00:22:03,380
她一次次遭遇阻力
Now, she's gotten resistance, time and again...

334
00:22:03,410 --> 00:22:05,630
来自退伍军人事务处的阻力
from the Veterans Affairs administration,

335
00:22:05,640 --> 00:22:07,730
来自她国会同事的阻力
from her colleagues in Congress...

336
00:22:07,790 --> 00:22:09,900
-能调大声点吗  -来自那些不希望
- Can you turn it up a bit? - ...from those who don't want to see

337
00:22:10,190 --> 00:22:13,270
政府给计划生育组织拨款的人
government funds going to Planned Parenthood.

338
00:22:13,270 --> 00:22:15,890
但是  她今天打给我时
And yet, when she called me today,

339
00:22:15,990 --> 00:22:19,870
她对建立这家诊所的热忱
she was just as passionate about this clinic as she was

340
00:22:19,870 --> 00:22:23,440
一如十年前她第一次跟我提出时那般
when she first brought it up to me ten years ago.

341
00:22:29,330 --> 00:22:33,290
桃瑞丝  你成功了
Well, Doris, it worked.

342
00:22:33,290 --> 00:22:36,030
我会跟退伍军人事务部长
I'll be working with the Secretary of Veterans Affairs,

343
00:22:36,030 --> 00:22:39,940
住房和城市发展部以及国会领袖合作帮你建立诊所
HUD and the congressional leaders to get you that clinic.

344
00:22:39,940 --> 00:22:42,970
因为你  我们将拯救生命
Because of you, we'll save lives.

345
00:22:55,640 --> 00:23:00,350
这正是美国人民想看到的领导
And that is exactly the sort of leadership the American people want.

346
00:23:00,420 --> 00:23:02,630
更多桃瑞丝·琼斯这样的领导人
More leaders like Doris Jones.

347
00:23:02,910 --> 00:23:05,420
等她任期结束退休时
And when she retires at the end of this term,

348
00:23:05,420 --> 00:23:08,380
我很高兴她女儿西莉娅
I'm delighted to say that her daughter, Celia,

349
00:23:08,390 --> 00:23:10,250
将竞选缺职
will run for the open seat

350
00:23:10,250 --> 00:23:13,620
像她母亲那样  继续实现人民的愿望
to continue delivering just like her mother has.

351
00:23:13,630 --> 00:23:15,750
不会吧
No fucking way.

352
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:21,080
我本人会
And I, for one, will support

353
00:23:20,870 --> 00:23:30,870
{\an8}2016国情咨文

354
00:23:21,080 --> 00:23:23,340
百分百支持你的竞选
your candidacy with everything I've got.

355
00:23:23,340 --> 00:23:25,620
我知道克莱尔也会的
And I know Claire will, as well.

356
00:23:31,030 --> 00:23:32,980
德州人百折不挠
Texans are tenacious.

357
00:23:33,050 --> 00:23:34,760
我很骄傲我娶了一位
I'm proud to be married to one,

358
00:23:34,760 --> 00:23:36,720
我很骄傲曾与琼斯议员女士
and I'm proud to have served with one,

359
00:23:36,720 --> 00:23:38,170
这样的德州人共事过
like Congresswoman Jones.

360
00:23:38,170 --> 00:23:41,000
谢谢你  桃瑞丝  谢谢你多年的服务
Thank you, Doris, for all your years of service,

361
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:44,180
也谢谢你  西莉娅  继承母亲的衣钵
and thank you, Celia, for picking up the mantle.

362
00:24:02,240 --> 00:24:04,450
桃瑞丝说是她女儿说话冒失
Doris said her daughter spoke out of turn,

363
00:24:04,450 --> 00:24:07,800
她对她和安德伍德协商的交易并不知情
that she didn't know about the deal she was brokering with Underwood.

364
00:24:07,900 --> 00:24:09,500
你跟莉安联络上了吗
Did you connect with LeAnn?

365
00:24:12,180 --> 00:24:13,750
没有
No, I didn't.

366
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:16,010
她说她得明天才能见我
She said she couldn't meet until tomorrow.

367
00:24:16,010 --> 00:24:17,930
现在也没必要了
Well, I guess there's no point now, anyway.

368
00:24:17,930 --> 00:24:19,720
如果是白宫在准备筹款
If the White House is orchestrating the funding,

369
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:21,590
安德伍德肯定不需要我帮忙
Underwood's not gonna want my help.

370
00:24:21,760 --> 00:24:24,520
该死  那笔钱本来能帮大忙的
Fuck! I really could've used that money.

371
00:24:24,540 --> 00:24:27,070
如果看上去像天上掉馅饼
Well, when it looks too good to be true...

372
00:24:27,150 --> 00:24:28,200
是啊  我知道
Yeah, I know.

373
00:24:29,580 --> 00:24:31,120
我什么时候能再见你
When am I gonna see you again?

374
00:24:34,120 --> 00:24:35,120
我不知道
I don't know.

375
00:24:36,530 --> 00:24:39,760
我有点...闷得发疯
I've been... feeling a bit stir-crazy.

376
00:24:40,940 --> 00:24:43,270
如果我退休了  或许该出去走走
If I'm retired, I should probably travel some.

377
00:24:43,900 --> 00:24:46,410
你可以去加州啊
Well, you could travel to California.

378
00:24:47,030 --> 00:24:49,310
11月之前  我会更多待在那边
I'll be there more than here until November.

379
00:24:49,650 --> 00:24:50,970
或许吧
Yeah, maybe.

380
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:53,940
不去也行
Or don't.

381
00:24:54,950 --> 00:24:56,360
你知道怎么联系我
You know how to reach me.

382
00:25:17,150 --> 00:25:18,460
你觉得是雷米吗
Do you think it was Remy?

383
00:25:18,470 --> 00:25:21,020
不太可能  我让他知道我们知道了
Highly doubtful. I made it clear what we knew.

384
00:25:21,020 --> 00:25:22,440
他知道你有证据吗
He knows you have proof?

385
00:25:22,440 --> 00:25:24,830
他知道我知道  不知道我有证据
He knows that I know. Not that I have proof.

386
00:25:24,830 --> 00:25:27,270
或许我们还不该把那张牌打出去
Maybe we shouldn't have played that card yet.

387
00:25:27,550 --> 00:25:29,160
雷米把事情都串起来了
Remy was connecting the dots.

388
00:25:29,160 --> 00:25:31,080
我必须让他打住
I needed to put the brakes on him.

389
00:25:31,080 --> 00:25:32,100
如果不是他
Well, if it wasn't him, 

390
00:25:32,100 --> 00:25:34,170
那肯定是桃瑞丝自己去找了弗兰西斯
Doris must've gone to Francis himself.

391
00:25:34,170 --> 00:25:35,330
她看到了机会就...
She saw an opening and--

392
00:25:35,330 --> 00:25:37,410
女士  计划有变
Ma'am, there's been a change of plans.

393
00:25:37,410 --> 00:25:39,670
等等  什么计划有变
Uh, hold on. What change of plans?

394
00:25:39,670 --> 00:25:41,730
我们带您回白宫
We're taking you back to the White House.

395
00:25:41,730 --> 00:25:43,540
不  我们得去安德鲁斯机场
No, we're going to Andrews.

396
00:25:43,550 --> 00:25:46,060
抱歉  这是总统的直接命令
I'm sorry, this is direct from the president.

397
00:25:48,050 --> 00:25:49,960
这不会像看上去那么困难
This is not gonna be as difficult as it seems.

398
00:25:49,960 --> 00:25:51,640
泰瑞明天一早就跟退伍军人事务处
Now, Terry's gonna be in touch with Veteran Affairs

399
00:25:51,640 --> 00:25:53,710
那边接触  起草修正案
first thing tomorrow to draft an amendment.

400
00:25:53,710 --> 00:25:56,670
如果共和党在委员会那里给我们阻力
And if the Republicans give us any resistance in committee,

401
00:25:56,670 --> 00:25:58,110
我就开始打电话找人
I'll start making calls.

402
00:25:58,110 --> 00:25:59,530
本轮会议结束之前
No reason why this can't get to the floor 

403
00:25:59,530 --> 00:26:01,010
完全可以呈递给国会
before the end of the session.

404
00:26:01,010 --> 00:26:03,270
谢谢你  总统先生
Well, thank you, Mr. President.

405
00:26:03,270 --> 00:26:06,060
谢你自己  你这手玩得漂亮
Thank yourself. You played this well.

406
00:26:06,090 --> 00:26:07,250
你怎么玩的
How did you play it?

407
00:26:07,250 --> 00:26:09,690
那是我们的小秘密了
Well, now, that's our little secret, isn't it?

408
00:26:09,830 --> 00:26:10,620
我送你出去
I'll walk you out.

409
00:26:10,620 --> 00:26:13,250
总统先生  我来吧
Uh, Mr. President, I got this. 

410
00:26:20,820 --> 00:26:22,030
克莱尔
Oh, Claire.

411
00:26:23,220 --> 00:26:26,340
总统的讲话多棒啊
Didn't the president make the most wonderful speech?

412
00:26:26,350 --> 00:26:28,410
是啊
Oh, he certainly did.

413
00:26:28,930 --> 00:26:31,560
多谢你说服总统
And I thank you for convincing the president

414
00:26:31,650 --> 00:26:34,420
在讲话中提到西莉娅
to mention Celia in his remarks.

415
00:26:34,420 --> 00:26:36,060
不客气
Well, it was my pleasure.

416
00:26:37,600 --> 00:26:38,980
-晚安  -晚安
- Good night. - Good night.

417
00:26:38,980 --> 00:26:39,980
晚安  克莱尔
Good night, Claire.

418
00:27:08,090 --> 00:27:09,380
我们说好的
We had a deal.

419
00:27:09,870 --> 00:27:10,900
我来了
I showed up.

420
00:27:10,970 --> 00:27:13,940
却利用这个机会给我的竞选拆台
And used that opportunity to undermine the campaign.

421
00:27:13,960 --> 00:27:15,410
你为什么不问我
Why didn't you just ask me?

422
00:27:15,410 --> 00:27:16,550
如果你需要用诊所说服桃瑞丝
If you needed the clinic to convince Doris--

423
00:27:16,550 --> 00:27:18,500
你根本不希望我竞选  弗兰西斯
You don't want me to run, Francis.

424
00:27:18,500 --> 00:27:21,580
是的  我不希望  但我们已经达成谅解了
That's right, I don't. But we'd reached an understanding.

425
00:27:21,610 --> 00:27:23,980
我觉得你就是说了你想让我听到的
I think you said what you wanted me to hear.

426
00:27:24,230 --> 00:27:25,840
那你误解我了
Well, then you misread me.

427
00:27:28,350 --> 00:27:31,460
我是在替自己着想  你也一样
I am looking out for myself. Just like you are.

428
00:27:31,460 --> 00:27:32,560
你为自己着想
And where did that get you,

429
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:35,540
而不是为我们两人着想的下场又如何
looking out for yourself instead of looking out for us?

430
00:27:35,770 --> 00:27:38,240
30选区现在没希望了  你明白的
The 30th is dead now. You know that.

431
00:27:38,340 --> 00:27:39,640
你觉得我会放弃吗
You think I'm giving up?

432
00:27:39,640 --> 00:27:41,470
怎么  你要跟琼斯母女竞争吗
What, you're gonna run against the Joneses?

433
00:27:41,470 --> 00:27:43,190
你会出丑的  克莱尔
You'll make a fool of yourself, Claire.

434
00:27:43,250 --> 00:27:44,960
即便他们支持你  你的胜算都不大
The odds were against you even with their blessing.

435
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:47,330
我本希望你自己能明白
Now, I hoped you'd reach that conclusion on your own.

436
00:27:47,330 --> 00:27:50,390
但你却对我撒谎
But instead, you lied to me.

437
00:27:52,460 --> 00:27:54,880
我没法逼你想通道理
Now, I can't force you to see reason.

438
00:27:55,680 --> 00:27:58,650
但我不允许你成为隐患
But I will not allow you to become dangerous.

439
00:28:11,740 --> 00:28:12,770
我也来一杯
I'll take one.

440
00:28:19,140 --> 00:28:20,100
喝我的吧
Take mine.

441
00:28:26,170 --> 00:28:27,280
克莱尔  听我说
Claire, look...

442
00:28:28,410 --> 00:28:31,330
我赢下大选后  我们就可以专注于
When I win the general, then we can concentrate

443
00:28:31,330 --> 00:28:34,180
为你在德州赢得参议员席位
on a Senate seat for you in Texas.

444
00:28:34,180 --> 00:28:36,670
你反正也不会想待在众议院
You don't want to be in the House, anyway.

445
00:28:36,670 --> 00:28:39,670
我们两人都没想到会出现海瑟·邓巴
And neither of us could have predicted a Heather Dunbar,

446
00:28:39,670 --> 00:28:41,590
那么厉害的对手
or how formidable she'd be.

447
00:28:41,780 --> 00:28:45,210
我们现在是在搏命
We are fighting for our lives here.

448
00:28:45,510 --> 00:28:50,200
等你竞选  你会希望处于有利地位
And when you run, you wanna do so from a position of strength.

449
00:28:50,820 --> 00:28:52,430
关键在于时机
It's about timing.

450
00:28:57,880 --> 00:29:00,510
或许是太早了  或许你是对的
Maybe it's too soon. Maybe you're right.

451
00:29:03,580 --> 00:29:04,850
但我得想想
But I need to think.

452
00:29:06,370 --> 00:29:07,400
好吧
Fair enough.

453
00:29:07,400 --> 00:29:08,870
我不能在这儿想
I can't do that here.

454
00:29:08,990 --> 00:29:10,280
回德州吗
Back in Texas?

455
00:29:10,930 --> 00:29:12,600
我不确定我得想多久
I'm not sure how long I'll need.

456
00:29:12,600 --> 00:29:14,340
需要多久都行
Well, take as long as you want.

457
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:18,030
我该走了
I should get going.

458
00:29:18,120 --> 00:29:20,360
已经挺晚了  你确定你不想留下过夜吗
It's late. You sure you don't want to spend the night?

459
00:29:20,370 --> 00:29:22,830
-母亲还在等我回去  -好吧
- Well, Mother was expecting me. - All right.

460
00:29:25,280 --> 00:29:27,450
我自己出去  你继续喝吧
I'll walk myself out. You enjoy your drink.

461
00:29:53,040 --> 00:29:53,970
以前有个男孩
You know, there was a boy

462
00:29:53,970 --> 00:29:55,920
就住在我加夫尼老家一个街区外的地方
that lived down the street from me in Gaffney.

463
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:58,580
跟我年纪差不多  他叫沃特·莱森
About my age. His name was Walter Wryson.

464
00:29:58,580 --> 00:30:01,530
他以前经常从家里跑出来  来我们家
He used to run away from home all the time and come to our house.

465
00:30:01,530 --> 00:30:03,050
并没什么充分的缘由
Not for any good reason.

466
00:30:03,050 --> 00:30:06,000
他爸爸不打他  也不愁吃穿
His daddy didn't beat him. He had clothes on his back.

467
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:07,790
莱森一家比我们有钱多了
The Wrysons had way more money than we did,

468
00:30:07,790 --> 00:30:09,040
但他还是要逃家
but run away he would, 

469
00:30:09,040 --> 00:30:11,290
每个月至少一次  直接跑来我们家
at least once a month and come straight to our place.

470
00:30:11,290 --> 00:30:14,520
一般  我母亲会打给他母亲
Now, usually, my mother would call his mother 

471
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:16,230
然后她就会来接他
and she'd come and fetch him.

472
00:30:16,230 --> 00:30:19,130
但到了第九第十次时
But about the ninth or tenth time this happened,

473
00:30:19,130 --> 00:30:22,990
沃特跑到外面  爬上了我们后院的一棵树
Walter ran outside, climbed up into a tree in our backyard,

474
00:30:22,990 --> 00:30:24,810
无论如何不肯下来
and wouldn't come down for nothing.

475
00:30:24,950 --> 00:30:26,430
我妈妈跟他妈妈说
Now, my mama said to his mama,

476
00:30:26,430 --> 00:30:27,990
"你让他在我们这儿待会儿吧
"Why don't you let us keep him for a while,

477
00:30:27,990 --> 00:30:29,960
直到他肯回家了"
until he feels like coming home?"

478
00:30:31,020 --> 00:30:35,230
但是  那小子可真是倔
But man, oh, man, that boy was stubborn.

479
00:30:36,550 --> 00:30:38,560
到了晚上  他还在树上
Night came, and he was still up there.

480
00:30:38,560 --> 00:30:41,520
不吃不喝  不拉屎
No food, no water... no toilet.

481
00:30:41,960 --> 00:30:43,330
我去睡觉之前
And just before I went to bed,

482
00:30:43,330 --> 00:30:45,740
我往窗外看  听到了他的哭声
I looked out my window and I heard him crying.

483
00:30:45,740 --> 00:30:48,580
我说  "沃特  你为什么不下来呢"
And I said, "Walter, why don't you come on down?"

484
00:30:48,580 --> 00:30:50,950
他就摇头  不肯
And he just shook his head no.

485
00:30:52,390 --> 00:30:54,570
第二天早晨  我醒来  往窗外一看
Well, the next morning, I woke up, I looked out the window

486
00:30:54,570 --> 00:30:56,680
沃特还在树上
and Walter was still up in that tree.

487
00:30:57,590 --> 00:31:01,120
于是早饭之后  我拿着一盘鸡蛋过去
So after breakfast, I walked over with a plate of eggs...

488
00:31:01,460 --> 00:31:03,160
问他是否想来点
and I asked him if he wanted some.

489
00:31:03,160 --> 00:31:05,270
他又摇头
And again, he just shook his head.

490
00:31:06,580 --> 00:31:07,900
我生气了
And I got angry.

491
00:31:08,860 --> 00:31:11,430
那小子有个好房子  好家庭
That boy had a good house, a good family,

492
00:31:11,430 --> 00:31:12,970
我求之不得的那种
the sort I would've killed for,

493
00:31:12,970 --> 00:31:14,540
他自己却不自知
and he didn't even realize it.

494
00:31:16,500 --> 00:31:19,410
于是我去工具棚  拿来把斧子
So I went into the tool shed and I took out an ax.

495
00:31:19,560 --> 00:31:21,230
我对沃特说
And I said to Walter...

496
00:31:21,380 --> 00:31:24,110
"你想知道住在我家究竟是什么感觉吗"
"You want to know what it's really like to live at my house?"

497
00:31:24,110 --> 00:31:26,060
我一顿狂砍那棵树
And I gave that tree a good whack.

498
00:31:26,060 --> 00:31:28,150
沃特大喊  但我没停手
And Walter cried out, but I kept on.

499
00:31:28,150 --> 00:31:28,890
你从没听过
I mean, you've never heard

500
00:31:28,890 --> 00:31:30,980
我砍树时  沃特发出的
screams like the one coming from Walter

501
00:31:30,980 --> 00:31:33,090
那样的尖叫
as I chopped at that tree.

502
00:31:33,830 --> 00:31:34,610
他都尿裤子了
He pissed his pants,

503
00:31:34,610 --> 00:31:36,370
淋了下来
and it came raining down on the ground,

504
00:31:36,370 --> 00:31:38,230
但我毫不在乎
but I didn't pay it no mind.

505
00:31:38,660 --> 00:31:40,590
我还继续砍
I just kept whacking away.

506
00:31:42,170 --> 00:31:43,070
于是
Well...

507
00:31:43,270 --> 00:31:44,970
没过多久沃特就下来了
it didn't take long before Walter was on the ground 

508
00:31:44,970 --> 00:31:46,590
跑回了自己家
and running back to his house.

509
00:31:46,690 --> 00:31:49,390
瞧  他不过就是需要点动力
You see, all he needed was a little motivation.

510
00:31:50,170 --> 00:31:52,180
所以我可以给克莱尔时间
So I'll give Claire some time.

511
00:31:52,790 --> 00:31:53,550
但为了她好
But for her sake,

512
00:31:53,550 --> 00:31:54,940
希望她能在我拿出斧子之前
I hope she comes out of her tree 

513
00:31:54,940 --> 00:31:57,120
就从她的树上下来
before I have to bring out my ax.

514
00:32:08,870 --> 00:32:11,790
他要我等着竞选参议员
He wants me to hold off for Senate.

515
00:32:12,590 --> 00:32:14,190
我告诉他我会考虑的
I told him I would think about it.

516
00:32:14,190 --> 00:32:17,530
-那么结束了吗  -不  没结束
- So it's over? - Oh, no, it's not over.

517
00:32:17,690 --> 00:32:20,080
他在全国电视上表示支持西莉娅
He endorsed Celia on national television.

518
00:32:20,090 --> 00:32:21,530
别去想30选区了
Forget the 30th.

519
00:32:22,190 --> 00:32:25,060
我们得往大想  就在本轮
We need to think bigger. This cycle.

520
00:32:28,090 --> 00:32:30,850
那我们得好好谈谈我的酬金问题了
Then we need to talk seriously about my compensation.

521
00:32:37,350 --> 00:32:38,920
-接通了吗  -是  先生
- He on? - Yes, sir.

522
00:32:47,410 --> 00:32:48,440
我准备好了
I'm ready.

523
00:32:48,530 --> 00:32:50,010
我这就给您接  先生
I'll connect you now, sir. 

524
00:32:50,390 --> 00:32:52,500
佩特罗夫总统  您现在在跟总统通话了
President Petrov, you are now on with the president.

525
00:32:52,500 --> 00:32:54,070
晚上好  总统先生
Good evening, Mr. President.

526
00:32:54,670 --> 00:32:56,510
早上好  总统先生
Good morning, Mr. President.

527
00:32:56,510 --> 00:32:57,900
你的讲话很棒
Your speech was good.

528
00:32:58,160 --> 00:32:59,600
或许有点太...
Perhaps, a bit too...

529
00:33:00,150 --> 00:33:01,460
乐观了
optimistic, hmm?

530
00:33:01,460 --> 00:33:03,350
我说的关于俄国的话都是真心的
I meant what I said about Russia.

531
00:33:03,350 --> 00:33:06,050
那只是空谈  没多大意义
It's just words. They mean very little.

532
00:33:06,050 --> 00:33:08,230
我愿意用实际行动支持我的言论
I'm willing to back them up with action.

533
00:33:08,230 --> 00:33:09,720
首先  我们该谈谈救市计划
First, we should talk about a bailout.

534
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:12,420
我愿意跟国际货币基金组织合作  帮你拿到所需
I'm willing to work with the IMF to get you what you need.

535
00:33:12,490 --> 00:33:14,930
其次  作为示好
And second, as a gesture of good faith,

536
00:33:14,930 --> 00:33:17,490
我们愿把伊戈尔·米尔金还给俄国
we'd like to return Igor Milkin to Russia.

537
00:33:17,490 --> 00:33:19,040
你早该送他回来了
You should've done so already.

538
00:33:19,040 --> 00:33:21,490
我需要你保证他会得到审判
I need your assurances he'll get a trial.

539
00:33:21,490 --> 00:33:24,090
-你在乎伊戈尔·米尔金干吗  -我不在乎
- What do you care about Igor Milkin? - I don't.

540
00:33:24,100 --> 00:33:25,240
你就是把他送去西伯利亚
You can send him to Siberia

541
00:33:25,240 --> 00:33:28,420
让他在矿井里死于黑肺病  我都不在乎
and let him die of black lung in a coal mine, for all I care.

542
00:33:28,420 --> 00:33:30,370
但我在乎你的经济
But I do care about your economy.

543
00:33:30,370 --> 00:33:32,310
你继续这么杀害受瞩目的商人
You keep killing high-profile businessmen 

544
00:33:32,310 --> 00:33:33,420
查抄他们的财产
and seizing their assets.

545
00:33:33,420 --> 00:33:35,360
-那样不...  -你是说叛徒吧
- That's no-- - You mean, traitors?

546
00:33:35,780 --> 00:33:38,070
听着  我知道他们在密谋造反
Look, I am aware that they were plotting a coup, 

547
00:33:38,070 --> 00:33:39,000
但那还是不...
but that still doesn't--

548
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:42,110
是的  因为是你策划的
Yes, because you orchestrated it.

549
00:33:42,660 --> 00:33:45,530
-什么  -否则米尔金为什么要飞去美国
- Excuse me? - Why else would Milkin fly to America?

550
00:33:45,530 --> 00:33:47,610
这事跟我们完全无关
We had nothing to do with this.

551
00:33:48,460 --> 00:33:50,790
你...在约旦河谷的事上就跟我撒过谎
You... you lied to me about the Jordan Valley,

552
00:33:50,790 --> 00:33:53,070
你在迈克尔·科里根的事上跟我撒了谎
you lied to me about Michael Corrigan.

553
00:33:54,390 --> 00:33:56,730
我不是想要推翻你  维克多
I am not trying to replace you, Viktor.

554
00:33:56,730 --> 00:33:59,220
我是想帮你  但你也得帮我
I'm trying to help you. But you have to help me.

555
00:33:59,220 --> 00:34:02,340
石油减产这样的威胁不会好使的
These threats of reducing your oil production, it won't work.

556
00:34:02,340 --> 00:34:05,040
你以为抬升能源价格会伤到我们
You think jacking up energy prices is gonna hurt us, 

557
00:34:05,040 --> 00:34:06,720
但那只是敲诈
but it's just extortion.

558
00:34:06,720 --> 00:34:09,080
我不会向敲诈低头的
And I will not respond to extortion.

559
00:34:09,080 --> 00:34:10,500
我可以把你的叛徒送回去
Now, I'll send your traitor back,

560
00:34:10,500 --> 00:34:11,450
但你不能再
but you've got to stop

561
00:34:11,460 --> 00:34:14,100
查抄公司  把人变没了
seizing companies and making people disappear.

562
00:34:14,100 --> 00:34:17,880
伊戈尔·米尔金比叛徒还糟糕  他是美国的傀儡
Igor Milkin is worse than a traitor. He's an American puppet.

563
00:34:18,090 --> 00:34:20,300
改朝换代  那才是敲诈
Regime change, that's extortion.

564
00:34:20,300 --> 00:34:23,270
是啊  但那是他们自己的行为  你是多虑了
Yes, but they acted on their own. You're being paranoid.

565
00:34:23,270 --> 00:34:25,180
送他回来  别开条件
Send him back. No terms.

566
00:34:25,180 --> 00:34:28,220
你如果不肯谈判  我们不会有进展的
We're not going to get anywhere if you're not willing to negotiate.

567
00:34:28,220 --> 00:34:29,140
那...
Well... 

568
00:34:29,910 --> 00:34:31,570
我们没话可说了
then I believe we're finished.

569
00:34:31,570 --> 00:34:35,100
是没什么可说了  谢谢  总统先生
And I believe you're right. Thank you, Mr. President.

570
00:34:37,870 --> 00:34:41,040
把米尔金安置在安全地点  他哪都不去
Put Milkin in a secure location. He's not going anywhere.

571
00:34:46,950 --> 00:34:48,020
米尔金先生
Mr. Milkin. 

572
00:34:49,180 --> 00:34:50,540
请你跟我来
I need you to come with me.

573
00:34:50,540 --> 00:34:51,520
我们去哪
Where are we going?

574
00:34:52,210 --> 00:34:53,810
羁押设施
A detainment facility.

575
00:34:53,940 --> 00:34:55,360
我不是要被遣返吧
I'm not being deported, am I?

576
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:58,050
不  我们要处理你的庇护请求
No, we're going to process your asylum request.

577
00:36:11,590 --> 00:36:12,560
克莱尔
Claire?

578
00:36:17,830 --> 00:36:20,550
如果你想抽烟  就抽吧
If you wanna smoke, you should smoke.

579
00:36:21,910 --> 00:36:23,500
我只是想抽一根
I only wanted one drag.

580
00:36:25,050 --> 00:36:29,640
他讨厌你以前拿着烟去马厩
He hated how you used to go down to the stables with your cigarettes.

581
00:36:31,450 --> 00:36:33,130
我不知道他知道这事
I didn't realize he knew.

582
00:36:33,440 --> 00:36:36,910
他那么爱你  你杀人他都不会在乎
He adored you. You got away with murder.

583
00:36:39,130 --> 00:36:40,690
你一直没睡等着我吗
Did you wait up for me?

584
00:36:40,770 --> 00:36:43,220
不  是药的关系
No, it's the medication.

585
00:36:43,490 --> 00:36:47,310
让我整天都感觉疲惫  然后又整宿睡不着
Keeps me tired all day, and then I'm up all night.

586
00:36:48,950 --> 00:36:52,260
我...看了讲话
I... I watched the speech.

587
00:36:52,930 --> 00:36:54,370
你打算怎么办
What are you gonna do?

588
00:36:55,200 --> 00:36:57,720
很晚了  母亲  我们早上再谈吧
It's late, Mother. Let's talk in the morning.

589
00:36:58,210 --> 00:37:03,030
对了  耳环真漂亮  我在电视上注意到了
By the way, those earrings are beautiful. I noticed 'em on TV.

590
00:37:04,750 --> 00:37:06,800
是弗兰西斯母亲的耳环
They're Francis' mother's earrings.

591
00:37:06,800 --> 00:37:10,020
-貌似不止一克拉  -两克拉
- They look like they're over a carat. - Two carats.

592
00:37:10,430 --> 00:37:12,270
她肯定从谁那儿偷来的
No doubt she stole them from someone.

593
00:37:14,770 --> 00:37:18,390
安德伍德一家永远能让人吃惊
The Underwoods never cease to amaze.

594
00:37:18,450 --> 00:37:19,400
母亲
Mother...

595
00:37:20,640 --> 00:37:22,880
我需要点钱
I'm going to need some money.

596
00:37:23,740 --> 00:37:25,150
给诊所吗  不是...
For the clinic? Isn't--

597
00:37:25,150 --> 00:37:28,320
150万  给莉安  还额外再需要一点
A million five for LeAnn and some on top of that.

598
00:37:28,860 --> 00:37:31,860
我以为你的竞选没戏了
Well, I thought your campaign was dead.

599
00:37:31,860 --> 00:37:34,590
是的  但我还是需要她为我工作
It is, but I still need her to work for me.

600
00:37:34,590 --> 00:37:37,910
但做什么呢  我可以向我的朋友借钱
But, what for? I mean, I can't ask my friends for money and--

601
00:37:37,920 --> 00:37:39,030
我们的钱
Our money.

602
00:37:43,510 --> 00:37:45,900
你是指我的钱
You mean my money.

603
00:37:47,120 --> 00:37:48,200
别跟我争
Don't fight me on this.

604
00:37:48,200 --> 00:37:49,960
爸爸会毫不犹豫地给我
Daddy would've done it, no questions asked.

605
00:37:49,960 --> 00:37:53,300
是啊  我没他那么傻
Yes, well... I'm not as foolish as he was.

606
00:37:53,300 --> 00:37:55,310
那我只能卖掉地产了
Well, I'll just have to sell the estate.

607
00:37:55,310 --> 00:37:56,470
什么
You what?

608
00:37:56,470 --> 00:37:59,360
钱在信托里  但地产是在我名下
The money is in the trust, but the land is in my name.

609
00:37:59,360 --> 00:38:02,450
-你不会敢的  -我在求你帮忙
- You wouldn't dare. - Well, I'm asking for your help.

610
00:38:02,450 --> 00:38:04,550
-如果你不肯  -帮忙
- If you refuse to give it-- - Help?

611
00:38:04,560 --> 00:38:08,130
我生病时你可完全没帮过我
You didn't lift a finger to help me when I got sick.

612
00:38:08,130 --> 00:38:09,740
你没告诉我你病了
You didn't tell me you were sick!

613
00:38:09,740 --> 00:38:12,000
因为你已经背弃了我
Because you had turned your back on me!

614
00:38:12,210 --> 00:38:15,140
你是那么让人失望
Oh, you are such a disappointment.

615
00:38:17,210 --> 00:38:18,190
你不希望我
You don't want me to sell

616
00:38:18,190 --> 00:38:20,800
背着你卖掉房子  但我会的
this house out from under you, but I will.

617
00:38:24,310 --> 00:38:25,910
我是你母亲
I am the mother.

618
00:38:26,220 --> 00:38:28,720
我是你母亲
I am the mother!

